    • dev - Tables supporting compilation of programs
      • dev.arch - System architecture

      • dev.htmlentity - Known HTML entity strings & codes
      • dev.include - A site where one file includes another
      • dev.license - Source code license
      • dev.linelim -

      • dev.msgfile - File in repo containing messages that should be normalized during CI
      • dev.noindent - Indicates that a file should not be automatically indented
      • dev.opt_type - Type of option (used in tool_opt)
      • dev.package - OpenACR package

      • dev.pkgkey - Keys belonging to the OpenACR package
      • dev.readme - File containing documentation

      • dev.scriptfile - Known script file
      • dev.srcfile - Source file or header (key is pathname)

    • dmmeta - Tables holding metadata (data model meta)
      • dmmeta.anonfld - Omit field name where possible (command line, enums, constants)
      • dmmeta.argvtype - Customize parsing of command lines (rarely used)
      • dmmeta.basepool - Specify pool to be used for allocating elements of a type
      • dmmeta.bitfld - Specify offset/width of a bitfield within another field
      • dmmeta.cafter - Control amc processing order for unrelated types (used in rare situations)
      • dmmeta.cascdel - Request cascading delete of referenced rows
      • dmmeta.ccmp - Generate hash function
      • dmmeta.cdflt - Specify default value for single-value types that lack fields
      • dmmeta.cextern - Externally defined ctype (a struct from system header, or from a c++ library)
      • dmmeta.cfast - FAST properties for ctype
      • dmmeta.cfmt - Specify options for printing/reading ctypes into multiple formats
      • dmmeta.cget - Generate state functions for these ctypes
      • dmmeta.charset - Generate functions to determine if a character is a member of a set
      • dmmeta.chash - Generate hash function
      • dmmeta.cppfunc - Value of field provided by this expression
      • dmmeta.cppkeyword - Built-in C++ keyword
      • dmmeta.cpptype - Specify whether a ctype can be passed by value, and other c++ options
      • dmmeta.csize - Specify size/alignment for built-in C++ types
      • dmmeta.cstr - Specify that type behaves like a string
      • dmmeta.ctype - Struct
      • dmmeta.ctypelen - Size of Ctype
      • dmmeta.dispatch - Generate code for a multi-way branch
      • dmmeta.dispatch_msg - Add message to a dispatch
      • dmmeta.dispctx - Use context with dispatch
      • dmmeta.dispfilter - Generate filter function on dispatch
      • dmmeta.dispsig - Cryptographic signature of all dispatches
      • dmmeta.dispsigcheck - Check signature of input data against executable’s version
      • dmmeta.disptrace - Generate trace fields (cycles, counts) for all dispatch branches
      • dmmeta.falias - Alias field
      • dmmeta.fastenc -
      • dmmeta.fastinstr -
      • dmmeta.fastop -
      • dmmeta.fbase - Customize imported Base fields
      • dmmeta.fbigend - Annotate field as having big-endian storage
      • dmmeta.fbitset - Generate bitset functions over integer field or array
      • dmmeta.fbuf - Buffer for reading/writing messages, works with Iohook
      • dmmeta.fbufdir - Buffer direction (in,out)
      • dmmeta.fbuftype - Buffer type
      • dmmeta.fcast - Generate implicit conversion from field to c++ expression
      • dmmeta.fcleanup - Request user-implemented function to be called at Uninit time for a field
      • dmmeta.fcmap - Bidirectional mapping between fconst values
      • dmmeta.fcmdline - Annotate field that holds process command line
      • dmmeta.fcmp - Request versionsort or case-insensitive sort for field
      • dmmeta.fcompact - Request compaction upon removal from index
      • dmmeta.fconst - Specify enum value (integer + string constant) for a field
      • dmmeta.fcurs - Request generation of custom cursor
      • dmmeta.fdec - Specify that field has an implied # of decimal places and specify formatting options
      • dmmeta.fdelay - Control elapsed time between execution of a step
      • dmmeta.ffast - FAST properties for field
      • dmmeta.fflag - Options for command-line flags
      • dmmeta.field - Specify field of a struct
      • dmmeta.findrem - Request generation of FindRemove function
      • dmmeta.finput - Describe input table of a program
      • dmmeta.fldoffset - Assert field offset - will result in compile-time error if violated
      • dmmeta.floadtuples - Request that process automatically load any input tables on startup
      • dmmeta.fnoremove - Omit any functions for removing elements from table; Table is append-only
      • dmmeta.foutput - Generate function to save index/table back to disk
      • dmmeta.fprefix - Mapping between field prefix and Reftype
      • dmmeta.fregx - Specify options for command-line regx field
      • dmmeta.fsort - Generate custom sort function for array field
      • dmmeta.fstep - Generate a main loop step to be executed whenever a field is non-empty
      • dmmeta.ftrace - Generate cycle/step counting fields for a step
      • dmmeta.ftuple -
      • dmmeta.func -
      • dmmeta.funique - This field must be unique in the table. Not needed for primary key
      • dmmeta.fuserinit - Add user-defined initialization function for field (see fcleanup)
      • dmmeta.fwddecl - Request forward declaration of a field
      • dmmeta.gconst - Import ssim table columns as fconst for a field
      • dmmeta.gstatic - Load entries for this table at startup time
      • dmmeta.gsymbol - Create C++ symbols from entries in ssim table
      • dmmeta.hashtype - Hash function type
      • dmmeta.hook - Required on Hook fields
      • dmmeta.inlary - Generate inline array of fixed or variable length (all entries fit within parent struct)
      • dmmeta.lenfld - Specify which gives length of varlen portion in bytes
      • dmmeta.listtype - Specify structure of linked list based on field prefix
      • dmmeta.llist - Options for Llist field
      • dmmeta.logcat - Log category
      • dmmeta.main - Generate Main function for namespace
      • dmmeta.msgtype - Specify message type for each eligible message, controls dispatch
      • dmmeta.nocascdel - Remove cascade delete for this index
      • dmmeta.nossimfile - Indicates that ssimfile does not exist for this ssimdb ctype
      • dmmeta.noxref - Explicitly specify that no x-ref exists between tables (don’t use unless forced)
      • dmmeta.ns - Namespace (for in-memory database, protocol, etc)
      • dmmeta.nscpp - Generate C++ code for this namespace
      • dmmeta.nsdb - Annotate ssimdb namespaces
      • dmmeta.nsfast - Whether namespace is FAST
      • dmmeta.nsinclude - Explicitly specify a C++ include file for namespace
      • dmmeta.nsjs - Generate JavaScript code for this namespace
      • dmmeta.nsproto - Annotate protocol namespace (collection of types, no state)
      • dmmeta.nstype - Namespace type
      • dmmeta.nsversion - Namespace version
      • dmmeta.nsx - Control code-generation and exception handling options for process/library
      • dmmeta.numstr - Add functions to read numbers out of a string field
      • dmmeta.pack - Request byte-packing of structure fields
      • dmmeta.pmaskfld - Specify which field holds presence mask bits (one for each field in struct)
      • dmmeta.pmaskfld_member - Explicit field-to-pmask association
      • dmmeta.pnew - Generate custom constructor (placement new), for use with binary protocols
      • dmmeta.pnewtype - Type of fbuf
      • dmmeta.printfmt - Print format
      • dmmeta.ptrary - Required for fields with reftype:Ptrary
      • dmmeta.reftype - Field type constructor (e.g. reference type)
      • dmmeta.rowid - Initialize field to row id of element
      • dmmeta.smallstr - Generated fixed-length padded or length-delimited string field
      • dmmeta.sortfld - Specify what field an index (Bheap,Atree) is sorted on
      • dmmeta.sorttype - Sort type
      • dmmeta.sqltype - Mapping of ctype -> SQL expression
      • dmmeta.ssimfile - File with ssim tuples
      • dmmeta.ssimreq - Extended constraints for ssim records
      • dmmeta.ssimsort - Define sort order for ssimfile
      • dmmeta.ssimvolatile - Types based on ssim files marked this way cannot be cross-referenced
      • dmmeta.steptype - Type of scheduler step
      • dmmeta.strfmt - Cfmt conversion type (misnomer, not necessarily a string)
      • dmmeta.strtype - Type of small string
      • dmmeta.substr - Specify that the field value is computed from a substring of another field
      • dmmeta.svtype - Table for determining ctype from separated value file
      • dmmeta.tary - Indirect linear dynamically alocated array (used for strings, arrays of data, etc)
      • dmmeta.thash - Hash index, required for fields with reftype Thash
      • dmmeta.tracefld - Trace fields
      • dmmeta.tracerec - Trace record
      • dmmeta.typefld - Specifies which field of a message carries the type
      • dmmeta.usertracefld - Add custom user trace fields to process’s trace struct
      • dmmeta.xref - Specify how to cross-reference (i.e. project, or group-by) one record with another

  174// --- amc.Enumstr.str.Lt
  175// Compare two fields. Comparison is anti-symmetric: if a>b, then !(b>a).
  176inline bool amc::str_Lt(amc::Enumstr& parent, amc::Enumstr &rhs) {
  177    return algo::RnullStr8_Lt(parent.str,rhs.str);
  178}
  179
  180// --- amc.Enumstr.str.Cmp
  181// Compare two fields.
  182inline i32 amc::str_Cmp(amc::Enumstr& parent, amc::Enumstr &rhs) {
  183    i32 retval = 0;
  184    retval = algo::RnullStr8_Cmp(parent.str, rhs.str);
  185    return retval;
  186}
  187
  188// --- amc.Enumstr..Hash
  189inline u32 amc::Enumstr_Hash(u32 prev, const amc::Enumstr & rhs) {
  190    prev = i32_Hash(prev, rhs.len);
  191    prev = RnullStr8_Hash(prev, rhs.str);
  192    return prev;
  193}
  194
  195// --- amc.Enumstr..Lt
  196inline bool amc::Enumstr_Lt(amc::Enumstr& lhs, amc::Enumstr& rhs) {
  197    return Enumstr_Cmp(lhs,rhs) < 0;
  198}
  199
  200// --- amc.Enumstr..Cmp
  201inline i32 amc::Enumstr_Cmp(amc::Enumstr& lhs, amc::Enumstr& rhs) {
  202    i32 retval = 0;
  203    retval = i32_Cmp(lhs.len, rhs.len);
  204    if (retval != 0) {
  205        return retval;
  206    }
  207    retval = str_Cmp(lhs,rhs);
  208    return retval;
  209}
  210
  211// --- amc.Enumstr..Init
  212// Set all fields to initial values.
  213inline void amc::Enumstr_Init(amc::Enumstr& parent) {
  214    parent.len = i32(0);
  215}
  216
  217// --- amc.Enumstr..Eq
  218inline bool amc::Enumstr_Eq(amc::Enumstr& lhs, amc::Enumstr& rhs) {
  219    bool retval = true;
  220    retval = i32_Eq(lhs.len, rhs.len);
  221    if (!retval) {
  222        return false;
  223    }
  224    retval = algo::RnullStr8_Eq(lhs.str, rhs.str);
  225    return retval;
  226}
  227
  228// --- amc.Enumstr..Update
  229// Set value. Return true if new value is different from old value.
  230inline bool amc::Enumstr_Update(amc::Enumstr &lhs, amc::Enumstr& rhs) {
  231    bool ret = !Enumstr_Eq(lhs, rhs); // compare values
  232    if (ret) {
  233        lhs = rhs; // update
  234    }
  235    return ret;
  236}

  433inline void amc::FCharset_Init(amc::FCharset& charset) {
  434    charset.charrange = bool(false);
  435    charset.calc = bool(false);
  436}

  438    amc::FChash_Init(*this);
  439}

  449    chash.ind_chash_next = (amc::FChash*)-1; // (amc.FDb.ind_chash) not-in-hash
  450}

  476// Set all fields to initial values.
  477inline void amc::FCpptype_Init(amc::FCpptype& cpptype) {
  478    cpptype.ctor = bool(false);
  479    cpptype.dtor = bool(true);
  480    cpptype.cheap_copy = bool(false);
  481    cpptype.p_ctype = NULL;
  482    cpptype.ind_cpptype_next = (amc::FCpptype*)-1; // (amc.FDb.ind_cpptype) not-in-hash
  483}

  522// --- amc.FCtype.zs_cfmt.EmptyQ
  523// Return true if index is empty
  524inline bool amc::zs_cfmt_EmptyQ(amc::FCtype& ctype) {
  525    return ctype.zs_cfmt_head == NULL;
  526}
  527
  528// --- amc.FCtype.zs_cfmt.First
  529// If index empty, return NULL. Otherwise return pointer to first element in index
  530inline amc::FCfmt* amc::zs_cfmt_First(amc::FCtype& ctype) {
  531    amc::FCfmt *row = NULL;
  532    row = ctype.zs_cfmt_head;
  533    return row;
  534}
  535
  536// --- amc.FCtype.zs_cfmt.InLlistQ
  537// Return true if row is in the linked list, false otherwise
  538inline bool amc::zs_cfmt_InLlistQ(amc::FCfmt& row) {
  539    bool result = false;
  540    result = !(row.zs_cfmt_next == (amc::FCfmt*)-1);
  541    return result;
  542}
  543
  544// --- amc.FCtype.zs_cfmt.Last
  545// If index empty, return NULL. Otherwise return pointer to last element in index
  546inline amc::FCfmt* amc::zs_cfmt_Last(amc::FCtype& ctype) {
  547    amc::FCfmt *row = NULL;
  548    row = ctype.zs_cfmt_tail;
  549    return row;
  550}
  551
  552// --- amc.FCtype.zs_cfmt.Next
  553// Return pointer to next element in the list
  554inline amc::FCfmt* amc::zs_cfmt_Next(amc::FCfmt &row) {
  555    return row.zs_cfmt_next;
  556}
  557
  558// --- amc.FCtype.zs_cfmt.qLast
  559// Return reference to last element in the index. No bounds checking.
  560inline amc::FCfmt& amc::zs_cfmt_qLast(amc::FCtype& ctype) {
  561    amc::FCfmt *row = NULL;
  562    row = ctype.zs_cfmt_tail;
  563    return *row;
  564}
  565
  566// --- amc.FCtype.c_bltin.InsertMaybe
  567// Insert row into pointer index. Return final membership status.
  568inline bool amc::c_bltin_InsertMaybe(amc::FCtype& ctype, amc::FBltin& row) {
  569    amc::FBltin* ptr = ctype.c_bltin;
  570    bool retval = (ptr == NULL) | (ptr == &row);
  571    if (retval) {
  572        ctype.c_bltin = &row;
  573    }
  574    return retval;
  575}
  576
  577// --- amc.FCtype.c_bltin.Remove
  578// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
  579inline void amc::c_bltin_Remove(amc::FCtype& ctype, amc::FBltin& row) {
  580    amc::FBltin *ptr = ctype.c_bltin;
  581    if (LIKELY(ptr == &row)) {
  582        ctype.c_bltin = NULL;
  583    }
  584}

  586// --- amc.FCtype.c_field.EmptyQ
  587// Return true if index is empty
  588inline bool amc::c_field_EmptyQ(amc::FCtype& ctype) {
  589    return ctype.c_field_n == 0;
  590}
  591
  592// --- amc.FCtype.c_field.Find
  593// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
  594inline amc::FField* amc::c_field_Find(amc::FCtype& ctype, u32 t) {
  595    amc::FField *retval = NULL;
  596    u64 idx = t;
  597    u64 lim = ctype.c_field_n;
  598    if (idx < lim) {
  599        retval = ctype.c_field_elems[idx];
  600    }
  601    return retval;
  602}
  603
  604// --- amc.FCtype.c_field.Getary
  605// Return array of pointers
  606inline algo::aryptr<amc::FField*> amc::c_field_Getary(amc::FCtype& ctype) {
  607    return algo::aryptr<amc::FField*>(ctype.c_field_elems, ctype.c_field_n);
  608}
  609
  610// --- amc.FCtype.c_field.N
  611// Return number of items in the pointer array
  612inline i32 amc::c_field_N(const amc::FCtype& ctype) {
  613    return ctype.c_field_n;
  614}

  725// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
  726inline void amc::c_static_RemoveAll(amc::FCtype& ctype) {
  727    for (u32 i = 0; i < ctype.c_static_n; i++) {
  728        // mark all elements as not-in-array
  729        ctype.c_static_elems[i]->ctype_c_static_in_ary = false;
  730    }
  731    ctype.c_static_n = 0;
  732}

  972    }
  973    return retval;
  974}
  975
  976// --- amc.FCtype.c_datafld.Getary
  977// Return array of pointers
  978inline algo::aryptr<amc::FField*> amc::c_datafld_Getary(amc::FCtype& ctype) {
  979    return algo::aryptr<amc::FField*>(ctype.c_datafld_elems, ctype.c_datafld_n);
  980}
  981
  982// --- amc.FCtype.c_datafld.N
  983// Return number of items in the pointer array
  984inline i32 amc::c_datafld_N(const amc::FCtype& ctype) {
  985    return ctype.c_datafld_n;
  986}
  987
  988// --- amc.FCtype.c_datafld.RemoveAll
  989// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
  990inline void amc::c_datafld_RemoveAll(amc::FCtype& ctype) {
  991    for (u32 i = 0; i < ctype.c_datafld_n; i++) {
  992        // mark all elements as not-in-array
  993        ctype.c_datafld_elems[i]->ctype_c_datafld_in_ary = false;
  994    }
  995    ctype.c_datafld_n = 0;
  996}

  998// --- amc.FCtype.c_datafld.qFind
  999// Return reference without bounds checking
 1000inline amc::FField& amc::c_datafld_qFind(amc::FCtype& ctype, u32 idx) {
 1001    return *ctype.c_datafld_elems[idx];
 1002}

 1126    bool retval = (ptr == NULL) | (ptr == &row);

 1514    amc::FCtypelen *ptr = ctype.c_ctypelen;
 1515    if (LIKELY(ptr == &row)) {
 1516        ctype.c_ctypelen = NULL;
 1517    }
 1518}
 1519
 1520// --- amc.FCtype.c_nossimfile.InsertMaybe
 1521// Insert row into pointer index. Return final membership status.
 1522inline bool amc::c_nossimfile_InsertMaybe(amc::FCtype& ctype, amc::FNossimfile& row) {
 1523    amc::FNossimfile* ptr = ctype.c_nossimfile;
 1524    bool retval = (ptr == NULL) | (ptr == &row);
 1525    if (retval) {
 1526        ctype.c_nossimfile = &row;
 1527    }
 1528    return retval;
 1529}
 1530
 1531// --- amc.FCtype.c_nossimfile.Remove
 1532// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
 1533inline void amc::c_nossimfile_Remove(amc::FCtype& ctype, amc::FNossimfile& row) {
 1534    amc::FNossimfile *ptr = ctype.c_nossimfile;
 1535    if (LIKELY(ptr == &row)) {
 1536        ctype.c_nossimfile = NULL;
 1537    }
 1538}
 1539
 1540// --- amc.FCtype.c_cfast.InsertMaybe
 1541// Insert row into pointer index. Return final membership status.
 1542inline bool amc::c_cfast_InsertMaybe(amc::FCtype& ctype, amc::FCfast& row) {
 1543    amc::FCfast* ptr = ctype.c_cfast;
 1544    bool retval = (ptr == NULL) | (ptr == &row);
 1545    if (retval) {
 1546        ctype.c_cfast = &row;
 1547    }
 1548    return retval;
 1549}
 1550
 1551// --- amc.FCtype.c_cfast.Remove
 1552// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
 1553inline void amc::c_cfast_Remove(amc::FCtype& ctype, amc::FCfast& row) {
 1554    amc::FCfast *ptr = ctype.c_cfast;
 1555    if (LIKELY(ptr == &row)) {
 1556        ctype.c_cfast = NULL;
 1557    }
 1558}
 1559
 1560// --- amc.FCtype.c_ffast.EmptyQ
 1561// Return true if index is empty
 1562inline bool amc::c_ffast_EmptyQ(amc::FCtype& ctype) {
 1563    return ctype.c_ffast_n == 0;
 1564}
 1565
 1566// --- amc.FCtype.c_ffast.Find
 1567// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
 1568inline amc::FFfast* amc::c_ffast_Find(amc::FCtype& ctype, u32 t) {
 1569    amc::FFfast *retval = NULL;
 1570    u64 idx = t;
 1571    u64 lim = ctype.c_ffast_n;
 1572    if (idx < lim) {
 1573        retval = ctype.c_ffast_elems[idx];
 1574    }
 1575    return retval;
 1576}
 1577
 1578// --- amc.FCtype.c_ffast.Getary
 1579// Return array of pointers
 1580inline algo::aryptr<amc::FFfast*> amc::c_ffast_Getary(amc::FCtype& ctype) {
 1581    return algo::aryptr<amc::FFfast*>(ctype.c_ffast_elems, ctype.c_ffast_n);
 1582}
 1583
 1584// --- amc.FCtype.c_ffast.N
 1585// Return number of items in the pointer array
 1586inline i32 amc::c_ffast_N(const amc::FCtype& ctype) {
 1587    return ctype.c_ffast_n;
 1588}
 1589
 1590// --- amc.FCtype.c_ffast.RemoveAll
 1591// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
 1592inline void amc::c_ffast_RemoveAll(amc::FCtype& ctype) {
 1593    for (u32 i = 0; i < ctype.c_ffast_n; i++) {
 1594        // mark all elements as not-in-array
 1595        ctype.c_ffast_elems[i]->ctype_c_ffast_in_ary = false;
 1596    }
 1597    ctype.c_ffast_n = 0;
 1598}
 1599
 1600// --- amc.FCtype.c_ffast.qFind
 1601// Return reference without bounds checking
 1602inline amc::FFfast& amc::c_ffast_qFind(amc::FCtype& ctype, u32 idx) {
 1603    return *ctype.c_ffast_elems[idx];
 1604}

 1609    return row.ctype_c_ffast_in_ary;
 1610}

 1615    return *ctype.c_ffast_elems[ctype.c_ffast_n-1];
 1616}

 1951// --- amc.FCtypelen..Init
 1952// Set all fields to initial values.
 1953inline void amc::FCtypelen_Init(amc::FCtypelen& ctypelen) {
 1954    ctypelen.len = u32(0);
 1955    ctypelen.alignment = i32(0);
 1956    ctypelen.padbytes = i32(0);
 1957    ctypelen.plaindata = bool(false);
 1958    ctypelen._db_c_ctypelen_in_ary = bool(false);
 1959}

 1961    amc::Genctx_Init(*this);
 1962}
 1963

 1965// --- amc.Genctx..Init
 1966// Set all fields to initial values.
 1967inline void amc::Genctx_Init(amc::Genctx& parent) {
 1968    parent.p_ns = NULL;
 1969    parent.p_ctype = NULL;
 1970    parent.p_field = NULL;
 1971    parent.p_tfunc = NULL;
 1972}

 1988// --- amc.FTclass.c_tfunc.Find
 1989// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
 1990inline amc::FTfunc* amc::c_tfunc_Find(amc::FTclass& tclass, u32 t) {
 1991    amc::FTfunc *retval = NULL;
 1992    u64 idx = t;
 1993    u64 lim = tclass.c_tfunc_n;
 1994    if (idx < lim) {
 1995        retval = tclass.c_tfunc_elems[idx];
 1996    }
 1997    return retval;
 1998}

 2067inline amc::FTfunc& amc::tclass_c_tfunc_curs_Access(tclass_c_tfunc_curs &curs) {
 2068    return *curs.elems[curs.index];
 2069}
 2070
 2071// --- amc.FTclass..Init
 2072// Set all fields to initial values.
 2073inline void amc::FTclass_Init(amc::FTclass& tclass) {
 2074    tclass.c_tfunc_elems = NULL; // (amc.FTclass.c_tfunc)
 2075    tclass.c_tfunc_n = 0; // (amc.FTclass.c_tfunc)
 2076    tclass.c_tfunc_max = 0; // (amc.FTclass.c_tfunc)
 2077    tclass.step = NULL;
 2078    tclass.ind_tclass_next = (amc::FTclass*)-1; // (amc.FDb.ind_tclass) not-in-hash
 2079}

 2081}

 2090// --- amc.FDb.fsort.Find
 2091// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
 2092inline amc::FFsort* amc::fsort_Find(u64 t) {
 2093    amc::FFsort *retval = NULL;
 2094    if (LIKELY(u64(t) < u64(_db.fsort_n))) {
 2095        u64 x = t + 1;
 2096        u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(x);
 2097        u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 2098        u64 index = x-base;
 2099        retval = &_db.fsort_lary[bsr][index];
 2100    }
 2101    return retval;
 2102}
 2103
 2104// --- amc.FDb.fsort.Last
 2105// Return pointer to last element of array, or NULL if array is empty
 2106inline amc::FFsort* amc::fsort_Last() {
 2107    return fsort_Find(u64(_db.fsort_n-1));
 2108}

 3817        u64 x = t + 1;

 3819        u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;

 3821        retval = &_db.pack_lary[bsr][index];
 3822    }

 4960}

 4962// --- amc.FDb.tracefld.Find
 4963// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
 4964inline amc::FTracefld* amc::tracefld_Find(u64 t) {
 4965    amc::FTracefld *retval = NULL;
 4966    if (LIKELY(u64(t) < u64(_db.tracefld_n))) {
 4967        u64 x = t + 1;
 4968        u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(x);
 4969        u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 4970        u64 index = x-base;
 4971        retval = &_db.tracefld_lary[bsr][index];
 4972    }
 4973    return retval;
 4974}
 4975
 4976// --- amc.FDb.tracefld.Last
 4977// Return pointer to last element of array, or NULL if array is empty
 4978inline amc::FTracefld* amc::tracefld_Last() {
 4979    return tracefld_Find(u64(_db.tracefld_n-1));
 4980}
 4981

 4984inline i32 amc::tracefld_N() {
 4985    return _db.tracefld_n;
 4986}

 5082// --- amc.FDb.c_dispsig_sorted.EmptyQ
 5083// Return true if index is empty
 5084inline bool amc::c_dispsig_sorted_EmptyQ() {
 5085    return _db.c_dispsig_sorted_n == 0;
 5086}
 5087
 5088// --- amc.FDb.c_dispsig_sorted.Find
 5089// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
 5090inline amc::FDispsig* amc::c_dispsig_sorted_Find(u32 t) {
 5091    amc::FDispsig *retval = NULL;
 5092    u64 idx = t;
 5093    u64 lim = _db.c_dispsig_sorted_n;
 5094    if (idx < lim) {
 5095        retval = _db.c_dispsig_sorted_elems[idx];
 5096    }
 5097    return retval;
 5098}
 5099
 5100// --- amc.FDb.c_dispsig_sorted.Getary
 5101// Return array of pointers
 5102inline algo::aryptr<amc::FDispsig*> amc::c_dispsig_sorted_Getary() {
 5103    return algo::aryptr<amc::FDispsig*>(_db.c_dispsig_sorted_elems, _db.c_dispsig_sorted_n);
 5104}
 5105
 5106// --- amc.FDb.c_dispsig_sorted.N
 5107// Return number of items in the pointer array
 5108inline i32 amc::c_dispsig_sorted_N() {
 5109    return _db.c_dispsig_sorted_n;
 5110}
 5111
 5112// --- amc.FDb.c_dispsig_sorted.RemoveAll
 5113// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
 5114inline void amc::c_dispsig_sorted_RemoveAll() {
 5115    for (u32 i = 0; i < _db.c_dispsig_sorted_n; i++) {
 5116        // mark all elements as not-in-array
 5117        _db.c_dispsig_sorted_elems[i]->_db_c_dispsig_sorted_in_ary = false;
 5118    }
 5119    _db.c_dispsig_sorted_n = 0;
 5120}
 5121
 5122// --- amc.FDb.c_dispsig_sorted.qFind
 5123// Return reference without bounds checking
 5124inline amc::FDispsig& amc::c_dispsig_sorted_qFind(u32 idx) {
 5125    return *_db.c_dispsig_sorted_elems[idx];
 5126}
 5127
 5128// --- amc.FDb.c_dispsig_sorted.InAryQ
 5129// True if row is in any ptrary instance
 5130inline bool amc::c_dispsig_sorted_InAryQ(amc::FDispsig& row) {
 5131    return row._db_c_dispsig_sorted_in_ary;
 5132}
 5133
 5134// --- amc.FDb.c_dispsig_sorted.qLast
 5135// Reference to last element without bounds checking
 5136inline amc::FDispsig& amc::c_dispsig_sorted_qLast() {
 5137    return *_db.c_dispsig_sorted_elems[_db.c_dispsig_sorted_n-1];
 5138}

 5146// --- amc.FDb.zs_sig_visit.First
 5147// If index empty, return NULL. Otherwise return pointer to first element in index
 5148inline amc::FCtype* amc::zs_sig_visit_First() {
 5149    amc::FCtype *row = NULL;
 5150    row = _db.zs_sig_visit_head;
 5151    return row;
 5152}
 5153
 5154// --- amc.FDb.zs_sig_visit.InLlistQ
 5155// Return true if row is in the linked list, false otherwise
 5156inline bool amc::zs_sig_visit_InLlistQ(amc::FCtype& row) {
 5157    bool result = false;
 5158    result = !(row.zs_sig_visit_next == (amc::FCtype*)-1);
 5159    return result;
 5160}
 5161
 5162// --- amc.FDb.zs_sig_visit.Last
 5163// If index empty, return NULL. Otherwise return pointer to last element in index
 5164inline amc::FCtype* amc::zs_sig_visit_Last() {
 5165    amc::FCtype *row = NULL;
 5166    row = _db.zs_sig_visit_tail;
 5167    return row;
 5168}
 5169
 5170// --- amc.FDb.zs_sig_visit.Next
 5171// Return pointer to next element in the list
 5172inline amc::FCtype* amc::zs_sig_visit_Next(amc::FCtype &row) {
 5173    return row.zs_sig_visit_next;
 5174}
 5175
 5176// --- amc.FDb.zs_sig_visit.qLast
 5177// Return reference to last element in the index. No bounds checking.
 5178inline amc::FCtype& amc::zs_sig_visit_qLast() {
 5179    amc::FCtype *row = NULL;
 5180    row = _db.zs_sig_visit_tail;
 5181    return *row;
 5182}

 5508    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(x);
 5509    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 5510    u64 index = x-base;
 5511    return _db.gen_lary[bsr][index];
 5512}

 5555
 5556// --- amc.FDb.tclass.AllocMem
 5557// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 5558inline void* amc::tclass_AllocMem() {
 5559    void *row = reinterpret_cast<amc::FTclass*>(_db.tclass_data) + _db.tclass_n;
 5560    if (_db.tclass_n == 51) row = NULL;
 5561    if (row) _db.tclass_n++;
 5562    return row;
 5563}
 5564
 5565// --- amc.FDb.tclass.EmptyQ
 5566// Return true if index is empty
 5567inline bool amc::tclass_EmptyQ() {
 5568    return _db.tclass_n == 0;
 5569}
 5570
 5571// --- amc.FDb.tclass.Find
 5572// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
 5573inline amc::FTclass* amc::tclass_Find(u64 t) {
 5574    u64 idx = t;
 5575    u64 lim = _db.tclass_n;
 5576    return idx < lim ? reinterpret_cast<amc::FTclass*>(_db.tclass_data) + idx : NULL; // unsigned comparison with limit
 5577}
 5578
 5579// --- amc.FDb.tclass.Getary
 5580// Return array pointer by value
 5581inline algo::aryptr<amc::FTclass> amc::tclass_Getary() {
 5582    return algo::aryptr<amc::FTclass>(reinterpret_cast<amc::FTclass*>(_db.tclass_data), _db.tclass_n);
 5583}
 5584
 5585// --- amc.FDb.tclass.Max
 5586// Return constant 51 -- max. number of items in the pool
 5587inline i32 amc::tclass_Max() {
 5588    return 51;
 5589}
 5590
 5591// --- amc.FDb.tclass.N
 5592// Return number of items in the array
 5593inline i32 amc::tclass_N() {
 5594    (void)_db;//only to avoid -Wunused-parameter
 5595    return _db.tclass_n;
 5596}
 5597
 5598// --- amc.FDb.tclass.qFind
 5599// 'quick' Access row by row id. No bounds checking in release.
 5600inline amc::FTclass& amc::tclass_qFind(u64 t) {
 5601    return reinterpret_cast<amc::FTclass*>(_db.tclass_data)[u64(t)];
 5602}
 5603
 5604// --- amc.FDb.tclass.rowid_Get
 5605// Compute row id of element given element's address
 5606inline u64 amc::tclass_rowid_Get(amc::FTclass &row) {
 5607    u64 ret = u64(&row - reinterpret_cast<amc::FTclass*>(_db.tclass_data));
 5608    return u64(ret);
 5609}

 6604
 6605// --- amc.FDb.c_substr_field.Find
 6606// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
 6607inline amc::FSubstr* amc::c_substr_field_Find(u32 t) {
 6608    amc::FSubstr *retval = NULL;
 6609    u64 idx = t;
 6610    u64 lim = _db.c_substr_field_n;
 6611    if (idx < lim) {
 6612        retval = _db.c_substr_field_elems[idx];
 6613    }
 6614    return retval;
 6615}
 6616
 6617// --- amc.FDb.c_substr_field.Getary
 6618// Return array of pointers
 6619inline algo::aryptr<amc::FSubstr*> amc::c_substr_field_Getary() {
 6620    return algo::aryptr<amc::FSubstr*>(_db.c_substr_field_elems, _db.c_substr_field_n);
 6621}
 6622
 6623// --- amc.FDb.c_substr_field.N
 6624// Return number of items in the pointer array
 6625inline i32 amc::c_substr_field_N() {
 6626    return _db.c_substr_field_n;
 6627}
 6628
 6629// --- amc.FDb.c_substr_field.RemoveAll
 6630// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
 6631inline void amc::c_substr_field_RemoveAll() {
 6632    for (u32 i = 0; i < _db.c_substr_field_n; i++) {
 6633        // mark all elements as not-in-array
 6634        _db.c_substr_field_elems[i]->_db_c_substr_field_in_ary = false;
 6635    }
 6636    _db.c_substr_field_n = 0;
 6637}
 6638
 6639// --- amc.FDb.c_substr_field.qFind
 6640// Return reference without bounds checking

 6663// --- amc.FDb.ctypelen.Find
 6664// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
 6665inline amc::FCtypelen* amc::ctypelen_Find(u64 t) {
 6666    amc::FCtypelen *retval = NULL;
 6667    if (LIKELY(u64(t) < u64(_db.ctypelen_n))) {
 6668        u64 x = t + 1;
 6669        u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(x);
 6670        u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 6671        u64 index = x-base;
 6672        retval = &_db.ctypelen_lary[bsr][index];
 6673    }
 6674    return retval;
 6675}
 6676
 6677// --- amc.FDb.ctypelen.Last
 6678// Return pointer to last element of array, or NULL if array is empty
 6679inline amc::FCtypelen* amc::ctypelen_Last() {
 6680    return ctypelen_Find(u64(_db.ctypelen_n-1));
 6681}

 6687}

 6707inline amc::FCtypelen* amc::c_ctypelen_Find(u32 t) {
 6708    amc::FCtypelen *retval = NULL;
 6709    u64 idx = t;
 6710    u64 lim = _db.c_ctypelen_n;
 6711    if (idx < lim) {
 6712        retval = _db.c_ctypelen_elems[idx];
 6713    }
 6714    return retval;
 6715}

 6721}

 6727}

 6729// --- amc.FDb.c_ctypelen.RemoveAll
 6730// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
 6731inline void amc::c_ctypelen_RemoveAll() {
 6732    for (u32 i = 0; i < _db.c_ctypelen_n; i++) {
 6733        // mark all elements as not-in-array
 6734        _db.c_ctypelen_elems[i]->_db_c_ctypelen_in_ary = false;
 6735    }
 6736    _db.c_ctypelen_n = 0;
 6737}

 7051// --- amc.FDb.cd_temp_func.InLlistQ
 7052// Return true if row is in the linked list, false otherwise
 7053inline bool amc::cd_temp_func_InLlistQ(amc::FFunc& row) {
 7054    bool result = false;
 7055    result = !(row.cd_temp_func_next == (amc::FFunc*)-1);
 7056    return result;
 7057}
 7058
 7059// --- amc.FDb.cd_temp_func.Last
 7060// If index empty, return NULL. Otherwise return pointer to last element in index
 7061inline amc::FFunc* amc::cd_temp_func_Last() {
 7062    amc::FFunc *row = NULL;
 7063    row = _db.cd_temp_func_head ? _db.cd_temp_func_head->cd_temp_func_prev : NULL;
 7064    return row;
 7065}
 7066
 7067// --- amc.FDb.cd_temp_func.N

 7069inline i32 amc::cd_temp_func_N() {
 7070    return _db.cd_temp_func_n;
 7071}

 7083}

 7640// --- amc.FDb.c_ssimfile_sorted.EmptyQ
 7641// Return true if index is empty
 7642inline bool amc::c_ssimfile_sorted_EmptyQ() {
 7643    return _db.c_ssimfile_sorted_n == 0;
 7644}
 7645
 7646// --- amc.FDb.c_ssimfile_sorted.Find
 7647// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
 7648inline amc::FSsimfile* amc::c_ssimfile_sorted_Find(u32 t) {
 7649    amc::FSsimfile *retval = NULL;
 7650    u64 idx = t;
 7651    u64 lim = _db.c_ssimfile_sorted_n;
 7652    if (idx < lim) {
 7653        retval = _db.c_ssimfile_sorted_elems[idx];
 7654    }
 7655    return retval;
 7656}
 7657
 7658// --- amc.FDb.c_ssimfile_sorted.Getary
 7659// Return array of pointers
 7660inline algo::aryptr<amc::FSsimfile*> amc::c_ssimfile_sorted_Getary() {
 7661    return algo::aryptr<amc::FSsimfile*>(_db.c_ssimfile_sorted_elems, _db.c_ssimfile_sorted_n);
 7662}
 7663
 7664// --- amc.FDb.c_ssimfile_sorted.N
 7665// Return number of items in the pointer array
 7666inline i32 amc::c_ssimfile_sorted_N() {
 7667    return _db.c_ssimfile_sorted_n;
 7668}
 7669
 7670// --- amc.FDb.c_ssimfile_sorted.RemoveAll
 7671// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
 7672inline void amc::c_ssimfile_sorted_RemoveAll() {
 7673    for (u32 i = 0; i < _db.c_ssimfile_sorted_n; i++) {
 7674        // mark all elements as not-in-array
 7675        _db.c_ssimfile_sorted_elems[i]->_db_c_ssimfile_sorted_in_ary = false;
 7676    }
 7677    _db.c_ssimfile_sorted_n = 0;
 7678}
 7679
 7680// --- amc.FDb.c_ssimfile_sorted.qFind
 7681// Return reference without bounds checking
 7682inline amc::FSsimfile& amc::c_ssimfile_sorted_qFind(u32 idx) {
 7683    return *_db.c_ssimfile_sorted_elems[idx];
 7684}
 7685
 7686// --- amc.FDb.c_ssimfile_sorted.InAryQ
 7687// True if row is in any ptrary instance
 7688inline bool amc::c_ssimfile_sorted_InAryQ(amc::FSsimfile& row) {
 7689    return row._db_c_ssimfile_sorted_in_ary;
 7690}
 7691
 7692// --- amc.FDb.c_ssimfile_sorted.qLast
 7693// Reference to last element without bounds checking
 7694inline amc::FSsimfile& amc::c_ssimfile_sorted_qLast() {
 7695    return *_db.c_ssimfile_sorted_elems[_db.c_ssimfile_sorted_n-1];
 7696}

 7704// --- amc.FDb.zd_ssimfile_todo.First
 7705// If index empty, return NULL. Otherwise return pointer to first element in index
 7706inline amc::FSsimfile* amc::zd_ssimfile_todo_First() {
 7707    amc::FSsimfile *row = NULL;
 7708    row = _db.zd_ssimfile_todo_head;
 7709    return row;
 7710}
 7711
 7712// --- amc.FDb.zd_ssimfile_todo.InLlistQ
 7713// Return true if row is in the linked list, false otherwise
 7714inline bool amc::zd_ssimfile_todo_InLlistQ(amc::FSsimfile& row) {
 7715    bool result = false;
 7716    result = !(row.zd_ssimfile_todo_next == (amc::FSsimfile*)-1);
 7717    return result;
 7718}
 7719
 7720// --- amc.FDb.zd_ssimfile_todo.Last
 7721// If index empty, return NULL. Otherwise return pointer to last element in index
 7722inline amc::FSsimfile* amc::zd_ssimfile_todo_Last() {
 7723    amc::FSsimfile *row = NULL;
 7724    row = _db.zd_ssimfile_todo_tail;
 7725    return row;
 7726}

 7732}

 7734// --- amc.FDb.zd_ssimfile_todo.Next

 7740// --- amc.FDb.zd_ssimfile_todo.Prev

 7743    return row.zd_ssimfile_todo_prev;
 7744}
 7745
 7746// --- amc.FDb.zd_ssimfile_todo.qLast

 7748inline amc::FSsimfile& amc::zd_ssimfile_todo_qLast() {

 7761// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
 7762inline amc::FCfast* amc::cfast_Find(u64 t) {
 7763    amc::FCfast *retval = NULL;
 7764    if (LIKELY(u64(t) < u64(_db.cfast_n))) {
 7765        u64 x = t + 1;
 7766        u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(x);
 7767        u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 7768        u64 index = x-base;
 7769        retval = &_db.cfast_lary[bsr][index];
 7770    }
 7771    return retval;
 7772}
 7773
 7774// --- amc.FDb.cfast.Last
 7775// Return pointer to last element of array, or NULL if array is empty
 7776inline amc::FCfast* amc::cfast_Last() {
 7777    return cfast_Find(u64(_db.cfast_n-1));
 7778}
 7779
 7780// --- amc.FDb.cfast.N
 7781// Return number of items in the pool
 7782inline i32 amc::cfast_N() {
 7783    return _db.cfast_n;
 7784}
 7785
 7786// --- amc.FDb.cfast.qFind
 7787// 'quick' Access row by row id. No bounds checking.
 7788inline amc::FCfast& amc::cfast_qFind(u64 t) {
 7789    u64 x = t + 1;
 7790    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(x);
 7791    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 7792    u64 index = x-base;
 7793    return _db.cfast_lary[bsr][index];
 7794}

11049inline amc::FDispatch::FDispatch() {
11050    amc::FDispatch_Init(*this);
11051}
11052
11053inline amc::FDispatch::~FDispatch() {
11054    amc::FDispatch_Uninit(*this);
11055}
11056
11057
11058// --- amc.FDispatch.c_dispfilter.InsertMaybe
11059// Insert row into pointer index. Return final membership status.
11060inline bool amc::c_dispfilter_InsertMaybe(amc::FDispatch& dispatch, amc::FDispfilter& row) {
11061    amc::FDispfilter* ptr = dispatch.c_dispfilter;
11062    bool retval = (ptr == NULL) | (ptr == &row);
11063    if (retval) {
11064        dispatch.c_dispfilter = &row;
11065    }
11066    return retval;
11067}
11068
11069// --- amc.FDispatch.c_dispfilter.Remove
11070// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
11071inline void amc::c_dispfilter_Remove(amc::FDispatch& dispatch, amc::FDispfilter& row) {
11072    amc::FDispfilter *ptr = dispatch.c_dispfilter;
11073    if (LIKELY(ptr == &row)) {
11074        dispatch.c_dispfilter = NULL;
11075    }
11076}
11077
11078// --- amc.FDispatch.c_dispatch_msg.EmptyQ
11079// Return true if index is empty
11080inline bool amc::c_dispatch_msg_EmptyQ(amc::FDispatch& dispatch) {
11081    return dispatch.c_dispatch_msg_n == 0;
11082}
11083
11084// --- amc.FDispatch.c_dispatch_msg.Find
11085// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
11086inline amc::FDispatchmsg* amc::c_dispatch_msg_Find(amc::FDispatch& dispatch, u32 t) {
11087    amc::FDispatchmsg *retval = NULL;
11088    u64 idx = t;
11089    u64 lim = dispatch.c_dispatch_msg_n;
11090    if (idx < lim) {
11091        retval = dispatch.c_dispatch_msg_elems[idx];
11092    }
11093    return retval;
11094}
11095
11096// --- amc.FDispatch.c_dispatch_msg.Getary
11097// Return array of pointers
11098inline algo::aryptr<amc::FDispatchmsg*> amc::c_dispatch_msg_Getary(amc::FDispatch& dispatch) {
11099    return algo::aryptr<amc::FDispatchmsg*>(dispatch.c_dispatch_msg_elems, dispatch.c_dispatch_msg_n);
11100}
11101
11102// --- amc.FDispatch.c_dispatch_msg.N
11103// Return number of items in the pointer array
11104inline i32 amc::c_dispatch_msg_N(const amc::FDispatch& dispatch) {
11105    return dispatch.c_dispatch_msg_n;
11106}
11107
11108// --- amc.FDispatch.c_dispatch_msg.RemoveAll
11109// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
11110inline void amc::c_dispatch_msg_RemoveAll(amc::FDispatch& dispatch) {
11111    for (u32 i = 0; i < dispatch.c_dispatch_msg_n; i++) {
11112        // mark all elements as not-in-array
11113        dispatch.c_dispatch_msg_elems[i]->dispatch_c_dispatch_msg_in_ary = false;
11114    }
11115    dispatch.c_dispatch_msg_n = 0;
11116}
11117
11118// --- amc.FDispatch.c_dispatch_msg.qFind
11119// Return reference without bounds checking
11120inline amc::FDispatchmsg& amc::c_dispatch_msg_qFind(amc::FDispatch& dispatch, u32 idx) {
11121    return *dispatch.c_dispatch_msg_elems[idx];
11122}
11123
11124// --- amc.FDispatch.c_dispatch_msg.InAryQ
11125// True if row is in any ptrary instance
11126inline bool amc::dispatch_c_dispatch_msg_InAryQ(amc::FDispatchmsg& row) {
11127    return row.dispatch_c_dispatch_msg_in_ary;
11128}
11129
11130// --- amc.FDispatch.c_dispatch_msg.qLast
11131// Reference to last element without bounds checking
11132inline amc::FDispatchmsg& amc::c_dispatch_msg_qLast(amc::FDispatch& dispatch) {
11133    return *dispatch.c_dispatch_msg_elems[dispatch.c_dispatch_msg_n-1];
11134}

11176// --- amc.FDispatch.c_dispatch_msg_curs.Reset
11177inline void amc::dispatch_c_dispatch_msg_curs_Reset(dispatch_c_dispatch_msg_curs &curs, amc::FDispatch &parent) {
11178    curs.elems = parent.c_dispatch_msg_elems;
11179    curs.n_elems = parent.c_dispatch_msg_n;
11180    curs.index = 0;
11181}
11182
11183// --- amc.FDispatch.c_dispatch_msg_curs.ValidQ
11184// cursor points to valid item
11185inline bool amc::dispatch_c_dispatch_msg_curs_ValidQ(dispatch_c_dispatch_msg_curs &curs) {
11186    return curs.index < curs.n_elems;
11187}
11188
11189// --- amc.FDispatch.c_dispatch_msg_curs.Next
11190// proceed to next item
11191inline void amc::dispatch_c_dispatch_msg_curs_Next(dispatch_c_dispatch_msg_curs &curs) {
11192    curs.index++;
11193}
11194
11195// --- amc.FDispatch.c_dispatch_msg_curs.Access
11196// item access
11197inline amc::FDispatchmsg& amc::dispatch_c_dispatch_msg_curs_Access(dispatch_c_dispatch_msg_curs &curs) {
11198    return *curs.elems[curs.index];
11199}

11284// Return true if index is empty
11285inline bool amc::c_fconst_EmptyQ(amc::FEnumstr& enumstr) {
11286    return enumstr.c_fconst_n == 0;
11287}
11288
11289// --- amc.FEnumstr.c_fconst.Find
11290// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
11291inline amc::FFconst* amc::c_fconst_Find(amc::FEnumstr& enumstr, u32 t) {
11292    amc::FFconst *retval = NULL;
11293    u64 idx = t;
11294    u64 lim = enumstr.c_fconst_n;
11295    if (idx < lim) {
11296        retval = enumstr.c_fconst_elems[idx];
11297    }
11298    return retval;
11299}

11304    return algo::aryptr<amc::FFconst*>(enumstr.c_fconst_elems, enumstr.c_fconst_n);
11305}

11335    enumstr.c_fconst_n = 0; // (amc.FEnumstr.c_fconst)
11336    enumstr.c_fconst_max = 0; // (amc.FEnumstr.c_fconst)
11337    enumstr.ind_enumstr_next = (amc::FEnumstr*)-1; // (amc.FDb.ind_enumstr) not-in-hash
11338    enumstr.bh_enumstr_idx = -1; // (amc.FEnumstrLen.bh_enumstr) not-in-heap
11339}

11379
11380// --- amc.FEnumstrLen.bh_enumstr.First
11381// If index empty, return NULL. Otherwise return pointer to first element in index
11382inline amc::FEnumstr* amc::bh_enumstr_First(amc::FEnumstrLen& enumstr_len) {
11383    amc::FEnumstr *row = NULL;
11384    if (enumstr_len.bh_enumstr_n > 0) {
11385        row = enumstr_len.bh_enumstr_elems[0];
11386    }
11387    return row;
11388}
11389
11390// --- amc.FEnumstrLen.bh_enumstr.InBheapQ
11391// Return true if row is in index, false otherwise
11392inline bool amc::bh_enumstr_InBheapQ(amc::FEnumstr& row) {
11393    bool result = false;
11394    result = row.bh_enumstr_idx != -1;
11395    return result;
11396}
11397
11398// --- amc.FEnumstrLen.bh_enumstr.N
11399// Return number of items in the heap
11400inline i32 amc::bh_enumstr_N(const amc::FEnumstrLen& enumstr_len) {
11401    return enumstr_len.bh_enumstr_n;
11402}
11403
11404// --- amc.FEnumstrLen..Init
11405// Set all fields to initial values.
11406inline void amc::FEnumstrLen_Init(amc::FEnumstrLen& enumstr_len) {
11407    enumstr_len.len = i32(0);
11408    enumstr_len.bh_enumstr_max   	= 0; // (amc.FEnumstrLen.bh_enumstr)
11409    enumstr_len.bh_enumstr_n     	= 0; // (amc.FEnumstrLen.bh_enumstr)
11410    enumstr_len.bh_enumstr_elems 	= NULL; // (amc.FEnumstrLen.bh_enumstr)
11411    enumstr_len.bh_enumstr_len_idx = -1; // (amc.FDb.bh_enumstr_len) not-in-heap
11412    enumstr_len.ind_enumstr_len_next = (amc::FEnumstrLen*)-1; // (amc.FDb.ind_enumstr_len) not-in-hash
11413}
11414
11415// --- amc.FEnumstrLen.bh_enumstr_curs.Access
11416// Access current element. If not more elements, return NULL
11417inline amc::FEnumstr& amc::enumstr_len_bh_enumstr_curs_Access(enumstr_len_bh_enumstr_curs &curs) {
11418    return *curs.temp_elems[0];
11419}
11420
11421// --- amc.FEnumstrLen.bh_enumstr_curs.ValidQ
11422// Return true if Access() will return non-NULL.
11423inline bool amc::enumstr_len_bh_enumstr_curs_ValidQ(enumstr_len_bh_enumstr_curs &curs) {
11424    return curs.temp_n > 0;
11425}

11657// --- amc.FField.c_fsort.InsertMaybe
11658// Insert row into pointer index. Return final membership status.
11659inline bool amc::c_fsort_InsertMaybe(amc::FField& field, amc::FFsort& row) {
11660    amc::FFsort* ptr = field.c_fsort;
11661    bool retval = (ptr == NULL) | (ptr == &row);
11662    if (retval) {
11663        field.c_fsort = &row;
11664    }
11665    return retval;
11666}
11667
11668// --- amc.FField.c_fsort.Remove
11669// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
11670inline void amc::c_fsort_Remove(amc::FField& field, amc::FFsort& row) {
11671    amc::FFsort *ptr = field.c_fsort;
11672    if (LIKELY(ptr == &row)) {
11673        field.c_fsort = NULL;
11674    }
11675}

12085// --- amc.FField.c_fconst.EmptyQ
12086// Return true if index is empty
12087inline bool amc::c_fconst_EmptyQ(amc::FField& field) {
12088    return field.c_fconst_n == 0;
12089}
12090
12091// --- amc.FField.c_fconst.Find
12092// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
12093inline amc::FFconst* amc::c_fconst_Find(amc::FField& field, u32 t) {
12094    amc::FFconst *retval = NULL;
12095    u64 idx = t;
12096    u64 lim = field.c_fconst_n;
12097    if (idx < lim) {
12098        retval = field.c_fconst_elems[idx];
12099    }
12100    return retval;
12101}
12102
12103// --- amc.FField.c_fconst.Getary
12104// Return array of pointers
12105inline algo::aryptr<amc::FFconst*> amc::c_fconst_Getary(amc::FField& field) {
12106    return algo::aryptr<amc::FFconst*>(field.c_fconst_elems, field.c_fconst_n);
12107}
12108
12109// --- amc.FField.c_fconst.N
12110// Return number of items in the pointer array
12111inline i32 amc::c_fconst_N(const amc::FField& field) {
12112    return field.c_fconst_n;
12113}
12114
12115// --- amc.FField.c_fconst.RemoveAll
12116// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
12117inline void amc::c_fconst_RemoveAll(amc::FField& field) {
12118    for (u32 i = 0; i < field.c_fconst_n; i++) {
12119        // mark all elements as not-in-array
12120        field.c_fconst_elems[i]->field_c_fconst_in_ary = false;
12121    }
12122    field.c_fconst_n = 0;
12123}
12124
12125// --- amc.FField.c_fconst.qFind
12126// Return reference without bounds checking
12127inline amc::FFconst& amc::c_fconst_qFind(amc::FField& field, u32 idx) {
12128    return *field.c_fconst_elems[idx];
12129}
12130
12131// --- amc.FField.c_fconst.InAryQ
12132// True if row is in any ptrary instance
12133inline bool amc::field_c_fconst_InAryQ(amc::FFconst& row) {
12134    return row.field_c_fconst_in_ary;
12135}
12136
12137// --- amc.FField.c_fconst.qLast
12138// Reference to last element without bounds checking
12139inline amc::FFconst& amc::c_fconst_qLast(amc::FField& field) {
12140    return *field.c_fconst_elems[field.c_fconst_n-1];
12141}

12839// --- amc.FField.c_ffast.Find
12840// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
12841inline amc::FFfast* amc::c_ffast_Find(amc::FField& field, u32 t) {
12842    amc::FFfast *retval = NULL;
12843    u64 idx = t;
12844    u64 lim = field.c_ffast_n;
12845    if (idx < lim) {
12846        retval = field.c_ffast_elems[idx];
12847    }
12848    return retval;
12849}
12850
12851// --- amc.FField.c_ffast.Getary
12852// Return array of pointers
12853inline algo::aryptr<amc::FFfast*> amc::c_ffast_Getary(amc::FField& field) {
12854    return algo::aryptr<amc::FFfast*>(field.c_ffast_elems, field.c_ffast_n);
12855}
12856
12857// --- amc.FField.c_ffast.N
12858// Return number of items in the pointer array
12859inline i32 amc::c_ffast_N(const amc::FField& field) {
12860    return field.c_ffast_n;
12861}
12862
12863// --- amc.FField.c_ffast.RemoveAll
12864// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
12865inline void amc::c_ffast_RemoveAll(amc::FField& field) {
12866    for (u32 i = 0; i < field.c_ffast_n; i++) {
12867        // mark all elements as not-in-array
12868        field.c_ffast_elems[i]->field_c_ffast_in_ary = false;
12869    }
12870    field.c_ffast_n = 0;
12871}
12872
12873// --- amc.FField.c_ffast.qFind
12874// Return reference without bounds checking
12875inline amc::FFfast& amc::c_ffast_qFind(amc::FField& field, u32 idx) {
12876    return *field.c_ffast_elems[idx];
12877}
12878
12879// --- amc.FField.c_ffast.InAryQ
12880// True if row is in any ptrary instance
12881inline bool amc::field_c_ffast_InAryQ(amc::FFfast& row) {
12882    return row.field_c_ffast_in_ary;
12883}
12884
12885// --- amc.FField.c_ffast.qLast
12886// Reference to last element without bounds checking
12887inline amc::FFfast& amc::c_ffast_qLast(amc::FField& field) {
12888    return *field.c_ffast_elems[field.c_ffast_n-1];
12889}

13237// --- amc.FFstep.c_fdelay.InsertMaybe
13238// Insert row into pointer index. Return final membership status.
13239inline bool amc::c_fdelay_InsertMaybe(amc::FFstep& fstep, amc::FFdelay& row) {
13240    amc::FFdelay* ptr = fstep.c_fdelay;
13241    bool retval = (ptr == NULL) | (ptr == &row);
13242    if (retval) {
13243        fstep.c_fdelay = &row;
13244    }
13245    return retval;
13246}
13247
13248// --- amc.FFstep.c_fdelay.Remove
13249// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
13250inline void amc::c_fdelay_Remove(amc::FFstep& fstep, amc::FFdelay& row) {
13251    amc::FFdelay *ptr = fstep.c_fdelay;
13252    if (LIKELY(ptr == &row)) {
13253        fstep.c_fdelay = NULL;
13254    }
13255}
13256
13257// --- amc.FFstep..Init
13258// Set all fields to initial values.
13259inline void amc::FFstep_Init(amc::FFstep& fstep) {
13260    fstep.c_fdelay = NULL;
13261    fstep.p_field = NULL;
13262    fstep.ns_c_fstep_in_ary = bool(false);
13263    fstep.ind_fstep_next = (amc::FFstep*)-1; // (amc.FDb.ind_fstep) not-in-hash
13264}

13283inline bool amc::funcarg_EmptyQ(amc::FFunc& func) {

13287// --- amc.FFunc.funcarg.Find
13288// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
13289inline amc::Funcarg* amc::funcarg_Find(amc::FFunc& func, u64 t) {
13290    u64 idx = t;
13291    u64 lim = func.funcarg_n;
13292    if (idx >= lim) return NULL;
13293    return func.funcarg_elems + idx;
13294}
13295
13296// --- amc.FFunc.funcarg.Getary
13297// Return array pointer by value
13298inline algo::aryptr<amc::Funcarg> amc::funcarg_Getary(const amc::FFunc& func) {
13299    return algo::aryptr<amc::Funcarg>(func.funcarg_elems, func.funcarg_n);
13300}
13301
13302// --- amc.FFunc.funcarg.Last
13303// Return pointer to last element of array, or NULL if array is empty
13304inline amc::Funcarg* amc::funcarg_Last(amc::FFunc& func) {
13305    return funcarg_Find(func, u64(func.funcarg_n-1));
13306}
13307
13308// --- amc.FFunc.funcarg.Max
13309// Return max. number of items in the array
13310inline i32 amc::funcarg_Max(amc::FFunc& func) {
13311    (void)func;
13312    return func.funcarg_max;
13313}
13314
13315// --- amc.FFunc.funcarg.N
13316// Return number of items in the array
13317inline i32 amc::funcarg_N(const amc::FFunc& func) {
13318    return func.funcarg_n;
13319}
13320
13321// --- amc.FFunc.funcarg.Reserve
13322// Make sure N *more* elements will fit in array. Process dies if out of memory
13323inline void amc::funcarg_Reserve(amc::FFunc& func, int n) {
13324    u32 new_n = func.funcarg_n + n;
13325    if (UNLIKELY(new_n > func.funcarg_max)) {
13326        funcarg_AbsReserve(func, new_n);
13327    }
13328}
13329
13330// --- amc.FFunc.funcarg.qFind
13331// 'quick' Access row by row id. No bounds checking.
13332inline amc::Funcarg& amc::funcarg_qFind(amc::FFunc& func, u64 t) {
13333    return func.funcarg_elems[t];
13334}
13335
13336// --- amc.FFunc.funcarg.qLast
13337// Return reference to last element of array. No bounds checking
13338inline amc::Funcarg& amc::funcarg_qLast(amc::FFunc& func) {
13339    return funcarg_qFind(func, u64(func.funcarg_n-1));
13340}
13341
13342// --- amc.FFunc.funcarg.rowid_Get
13343// Return row id of specified element
13344inline u64 amc::funcarg_rowid_Get(amc::FFunc& func, amc::Funcarg &elem) {
13345    u64 id = &elem - func.funcarg_elems;
13346    return u64(id);
13347}

13400    fwddecl.ind_fwddecl_next = (amc::FFwddecl*)-1; // (amc.FDb.ind_fwddecl) not-in-hash
13401}

13427// --- amc.FGen.step.Call
13428// Invoke function by pointer
13429inline void amc::step_Call(amc::FGen& gen) {
13430    if (gen.step) {
13431        gen.step();
13432    }
13433}

13441    gen.step = NULL;
13442}

13455    return parent.ind_seen_n == 0;
13456}

13458// --- amc.FGenXref.ind_seen.N
13459// Return number of items in the hash
13460inline i32 amc::ind_seen_N(const amc::FGenXref& parent) {
13461    return parent.ind_seen_n;
13462}
13463
13464// --- amc.FGenXref.seen.EmptyQ
13465// Return true if index is empty
13466inline bool amc::seen_EmptyQ(amc::FGenXref& parent) {
13467    return parent.seen_n == 0;
13468}
13469
13470// --- amc.FGenXref.seen.Find
13471// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
13472inline amc::FGenXrefSeen* amc::seen_Find(amc::FGenXref& parent, u64 t) {
13473    amc::FGenXrefSeen *retval = NULL;
13474    if (LIKELY(u64(t) < u64(parent.seen_n))) {
13475        u64 x = t + 1;
13476        u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(x);
13477        u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
13478        u64 index = x-base;
13479        retval = &parent.seen_lary[bsr][index];
13480    }
13481    return retval;
13482}
13483
13484// --- amc.FGenXref.seen.Last
13485// Return pointer to last element of array, or NULL if array is empty
13486inline amc::FGenXrefSeen* amc::seen_Last(amc::FGenXref& parent) {
13487    return seen_Find(parent, u64(parent.seen_n-1));
13488}
13489
13490// --- amc.FGenXref.seen.N
13491// Return number of items in the pool
13492inline i32 amc::seen_N(const amc::FGenXref& parent) {
13493    return parent.seen_n;
13494}
13495
13496// --- amc.FGenXref.seen.qFind
13497// 'quick' Access row by row id. No bounds checking.
13498inline amc::FGenXrefSeen& amc::seen_qFind(amc::FGenXref& parent, u64 t) {
13499    u64 x = t + 1;
13500    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(x);
13501    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
13502    u64 index = x-base;
13503    return parent.seen_lary[bsr][index];
13504}
13505
13506// --- amc.FGenXref.seen_curs.Reset
13507// cursor points to valid item
13508inline void amc::FGenXref_seen_curs_Reset(FGenXref_seen_curs &curs, amc::FGenXref &parent) {
13509    curs.parent = &parent;
13510    curs.index = 0;
13511}
13512
13513// --- amc.FGenXref.seen_curs.ValidQ
13514// cursor points to valid item
13515inline bool amc::FGenXref_seen_curs_ValidQ(FGenXref_seen_curs &curs) {
13516    return curs.index < (*curs.parent).seen_n;
13517}
13518
13519// --- amc.FGenXref.seen_curs.Next
13520// proceed to next item
13521inline void amc::FGenXref_seen_curs_Next(FGenXref_seen_curs &curs) {
13522    curs.index++;
13523}
13524
13525// --- amc.FGenXref.seen_curs.Access
13526// item access
13527inline amc::FGenXrefSeen& amc::FGenXref_seen_curs_Access(FGenXref_seen_curs &curs) {
13528    return seen_qFind((*curs.parent), u64(curs.index));
13529}

13731// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
13732inline amc::FCtype* amc::c_ctype_Find(amc::FNs& ns, u32 t) {
13733    amc::FCtype *retval = NULL;
13734    u64 idx = t;
13735    u64 lim = ns.c_ctype_n;
13736    if (idx < lim) {
13737        retval = ns.c_ctype_elems[idx];
13738    }
13739    return retval;
13740}

13756inline void amc::c_ctype_RemoveAll(amc::FNs& ns) {

13758        // mark all elements as not-in-array

13760    }
13761    ns.c_ctype_n = 0;
13762}

13898// --- amc.FNs.c_globfld.InsertMaybe
13899// Insert row into pointer index. Return final membership status.
13900inline bool amc::c_globfld_InsertMaybe(amc::FNs& ns, amc::FField& row) {
13901    amc::FField* ptr = ns.c_globfld;
13902    bool retval = (ptr == NULL) | (ptr == &row);
13903    if (retval) {
13904        ns.c_globfld = &row;
13905    }
13906    return retval;
13907}
13908
13909// --- amc.FNs.c_globfld.Remove
13910// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
13911inline void amc::c_globfld_Remove(amc::FNs& ns, amc::FField& row) {
13912    amc::FField *ptr = ns.c_globfld;
13913    if (LIKELY(ptr == &row)) {
13914        ns.c_globfld = NULL;
13915    }
13916}

13976// --- amc.FNs.c_main.InsertMaybe
13977// Insert row into pointer index. Return final membership status.
13978inline bool amc::c_main_InsertMaybe(amc::FNs& ns, amc::FMain& row) {
13979    amc::FMain* ptr = ns.c_main;
13980    bool retval = (ptr == NULL) | (ptr == &row);
13981    if (retval) {
13982        ns.c_main = &row;
13983    }
13984    return retval;
13985}
13986
13987// --- amc.FNs.c_main.Remove
13988// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
13989inline void amc::c_main_Remove(amc::FNs& ns, amc::FMain& row) {
13990    amc::FMain *ptr = ns.c_main;
13991    if (LIKELY(ptr == &row)) {
13992        ns.c_main = NULL;
13993    }
13994}
13995
13996// --- amc.FNs.include.EmptyQ
13997// Return true if index is empty
13998inline bool amc::include_EmptyQ(amc::FNs& ns) {
13999    return ns.include_n == 0;
14000}
14001
14002// --- amc.FNs.include.Find
14003// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
14004inline algo::cstring* amc::include_Find(amc::FNs& ns, u64 t) {
14005    u64 idx = t;
14006    u64 lim = ns.include_n;
14007    if (idx >= lim) return NULL;
14008    return ns.include_elems + idx;
14009}
14010
14011// --- amc.FNs.include.Getary
14012// Return array pointer by value
14013inline algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> amc::include_Getary(const amc::FNs& ns) {
14014    return algo::aryptr<algo::cstring>(ns.include_elems, ns.include_n);
14015}
14016
14017// --- amc.FNs.include.Last
14018// Return pointer to last element of array, or NULL if array is empty
14019inline algo::cstring* amc::include_Last(amc::FNs& ns) {
14020    return include_Find(ns, u64(ns.include_n-1));
14021}
14022
14023// --- amc.FNs.include.Max
14024// Return max. number of items in the array
14025inline i32 amc::include_Max(amc::FNs& ns) {
14026    (void)ns;
14027    return ns.include_max;
14028}
14029
14030// --- amc.FNs.include.N
14031// Return number of items in the array
14032inline i32 amc::include_N(const amc::FNs& ns) {
14033    return ns.include_n;
14034}
14035
14036// --- amc.FNs.include.Reserve
14037// Make sure N *more* elements will fit in array. Process dies if out of memory
14038inline void amc::include_Reserve(amc::FNs& ns, int n) {
14039    u32 new_n = ns.include_n + n;
14040    if (UNLIKELY(new_n > ns.include_max)) {
14041        include_AbsReserve(ns, new_n);
14042    }
14043}
14044
14045// --- amc.FNs.include.qFind
14046// 'quick' Access row by row id. No bounds checking.
14047inline algo::cstring& amc::include_qFind(amc::FNs& ns, u64 t) {
14048    return ns.include_elems[t];
14049}
14050
14051// --- amc.FNs.include.qLast
14052// Return reference to last element of array. No bounds checking
14053inline algo::cstring& amc::include_qLast(amc::FNs& ns) {
14054    return include_qFind(ns, u64(ns.include_n-1));
14055}
14056
14057// --- amc.FNs.include.rowid_Get
14058// Return row id of specified element
14059inline u64 amc::include_rowid_Get(amc::FNs& ns, algo::cstring &elem) {
14060    u64 id = &elem - ns.include_elems;
14061    return u64(id);
14062}

14070// --- amc.FNs.c_dispsig.Find
14071// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
14072inline amc::FDispsig* amc::c_dispsig_Find(amc::FNs& ns, u32 t) {
14073    amc::FDispsig *retval = NULL;
14074    u64 idx = t;
14075    u64 lim = ns.c_dispsig_n;
14076    if (idx < lim) {
14077        retval = ns.c_dispsig_elems[idx];
14078    }
14079    return retval;
14080}

14082// --- amc.FNs.c_dispsig.Getary
14083// Return array of pointers

14085    return algo::aryptr<amc::FDispsig*>(ns.c_dispsig_elems, ns.c_dispsig_n);

14091    return ns.c_dispsig_n;
14092}
14093
14094// --- amc.FNs.c_dispsig.RemoveAll
14095// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
14096inline void amc::c_dispsig_RemoveAll(amc::FNs& ns) {
14097    for (u32 i = 0; i < ns.c_dispsig_n; i++) {
14098        // mark all elements as not-in-array
14099        ns.c_dispsig_elems[i]->ns_c_dispsig_in_ary = false;
14100    }
14101    ns.c_dispsig_n = 0;
14102}
14103
14104// --- amc.FNs.c_dispsig.qFind
14105// Return reference without bounds checking
14106inline amc::FDispsig& amc::c_dispsig_qFind(amc::FNs& ns, u32 idx) {
14107    return *ns.c_dispsig_elems[idx];
14108}

14112inline bool amc::ns_c_dispsig_InAryQ(amc::FDispsig& row) {
14113    return row.ns_c_dispsig_in_ary;
14114}

14119    return *ns.c_dispsig_elems[ns.c_dispsig_n-1];
14120}

14771
14772// --- amc.FNs.c_nscpp.InsertMaybe
14773// Insert row into pointer index. Return final membership status.
14774inline bool amc::c_nscpp_InsertMaybe(amc::FNs& ns, amc::FNscpp& row) {
14775    amc::FNscpp* ptr = ns.c_nscpp;
14776    bool retval = (ptr == NULL) | (ptr == &row);
14777    if (retval) {
14778        ns.c_nscpp = &row;
14779    }
14780    return retval;
14781}
14782
14783// --- amc.FNs.c_nscpp.Remove
14784// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
14785inline void amc::c_nscpp_Remove(amc::FNs& ns, amc::FNscpp& row) {
14786    amc::FNscpp *ptr = ns.c_nscpp;
14787    if (LIKELY(ptr == &row)) {
14788        ns.c_nscpp = NULL;
14789    }
14790}

15304// --- amc.FPmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member.EmptyQ
15305// Return true if index is empty
15306inline bool amc::c_pmaskfld_member_EmptyQ(amc::FPmaskfld& pmaskfld) {
15307    return pmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member_n == 0;
15308}
15309
15310// --- amc.FPmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member.Find
15311// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
15312inline amc::FPmaskfldMember* amc::c_pmaskfld_member_Find(amc::FPmaskfld& pmaskfld, u32 t) {
15313    amc::FPmaskfldMember *retval = NULL;
15314    u64 idx = t;
15315    u64 lim = pmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member_n;
15316    if (idx < lim) {
15317        retval = pmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member_elems[idx];
15318    }
15319    return retval;
15320}
15321
15322// --- amc.FPmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member.Getary
15323// Return array of pointers
15324inline algo::aryptr<amc::FPmaskfldMember*> amc::c_pmaskfld_member_Getary(amc::FPmaskfld& pmaskfld) {
15325    return algo::aryptr<amc::FPmaskfldMember*>(pmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member_elems, pmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member_n);
15326}
15327
15328// --- amc.FPmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member.N
15329// Return number of items in the pointer array
15330inline i32 amc::c_pmaskfld_member_N(const amc::FPmaskfld& pmaskfld) {
15331    return pmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member_n;
15332}
15333
15334// --- amc.FPmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member.RemoveAll
15335// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
15336inline void amc::c_pmaskfld_member_RemoveAll(amc::FPmaskfld& pmaskfld) {
15337    for (u32 i = 0; i < pmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member_n; i++) {
15338        // mark all elements as not-in-array
15339        pmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member_elems[i]->pmaskfld_c_pmaskfld_member_in_ary = false;
15340    }
15341    pmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member_n = 0;
15342}
15343
15344// --- amc.FPmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member.qFind
15345// Return reference without bounds checking
15346inline amc::FPmaskfldMember& amc::c_pmaskfld_member_qFind(amc::FPmaskfld& pmaskfld, u32 idx) {
15347    return *pmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member_elems[idx];
15348}
15349
15350// --- amc.FPmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member.InAryQ
15351// True if row is in any ptrary instance
15352inline bool amc::pmaskfld_c_pmaskfld_member_InAryQ(amc::FPmaskfldMember& row) {
15353    return row.pmaskfld_c_pmaskfld_member_in_ary;
15354}
15355
15356// --- amc.FPmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member.qLast
15357// Reference to last element without bounds checking
15358inline amc::FPmaskfldMember& amc::c_pmaskfld_member_qLast(amc::FPmaskfld& pmaskfld) {
15359    return *pmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member_elems[pmaskfld.c_pmaskfld_member_n-1];
15360}

15373}

15464// --- amc.FReftype.zs_fprefix.First
15465// If index empty, return NULL. Otherwise return pointer to first element in index

15471
15472// --- amc.FReftype.zs_fprefix.InLlistQ
15473// Return true if row is in the linked list, false otherwise
15474inline bool amc::zs_fprefix_InLlistQ(amc::FFprefix& row) {
15475    bool result = false;
15476    result = !(row.zs_fprefix_next == (amc::FFprefix*)-1);
15477    return result;
15478}

15480// --- amc.FReftype.zs_fprefix.Last
15481// If index empty, return NULL. Otherwise return pointer to last element in index
15482inline amc::FFprefix* amc::zs_fprefix_Last(amc::FReftype& reftype) {
15483    amc::FFprefix *row = NULL;
15484    row = reftype.zs_fprefix_tail;
15485    return row;
15486}

15549// --- amc.FSmallstr.c_numstr.InsertMaybe
15550// Insert row into pointer index. Return final membership status.
15551inline bool amc::c_numstr_InsertMaybe(amc::FSmallstr& smallstr, amc::FNumstr& row) {
15552    amc::FNumstr* ptr = smallstr.c_numstr;
15553    bool retval = (ptr == NULL) | (ptr == &row);
15554    if (retval) {
15555        smallstr.c_numstr = &row;
15556    }
15557    return retval;
15558}
15559
15560// --- amc.FSmallstr.c_numstr.Remove
15561// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
15562inline void amc::c_numstr_Remove(amc::FSmallstr& smallstr, amc::FNumstr& row) {
15563    amc::FNumstr *ptr = smallstr.c_numstr;
15564    if (LIKELY(ptr == &row)) {
15565        smallstr.c_numstr = NULL;
15566    }
15567}

15574    smallstr.p_field = NULL;
15575    smallstr.c_numstr = NULL;
15576    smallstr.ind_smallstr_next = (amc::FSmallstr*)-1; // (amc.FDb.ind_smallstr) not-in-hash
15577}

15696// --- amc.FTarget.c_targdep.EmptyQ
15697// Return true if index is empty
15698inline bool amc::c_targdep_EmptyQ(amc::FTarget& target) {
15699    return target.c_targdep_n == 0;
15700}
15701
15702// --- amc.FTarget.c_targdep.Find
15703// Look up row by row id. Return NULL if out of range
15704inline amc::FTargdep* amc::c_targdep_Find(amc::FTarget& target, u32 t) {
15705    amc::FTargdep *retval = NULL;
15706    u64 idx = t;
15707    u64 lim = target.c_targdep_n;
15708    if (idx < lim) {
15709        retval = target.c_targdep_elems[idx];
15710    }
15711    return retval;
15712}
15713
15714// --- amc.FTarget.c_targdep.Getary
15715// Return array of pointers
15716inline algo::aryptr<amc::FTargdep*> amc::c_targdep_Getary(amc::FTarget& target) {
15717    return algo::aryptr<amc::FTargdep*>(target.c_targdep_elems, target.c_targdep_n);
15718}
15719
15720// --- amc.FTarget.c_targdep.N
15721// Return number of items in the pointer array
15722inline i32 amc::c_targdep_N(const amc::FTarget& target) {
15723    return target.c_targdep_n;
15724}
15725
15726// --- amc.FTarget.c_targdep.RemoveAll
15727// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
15728inline void amc::c_targdep_RemoveAll(amc::FTarget& target) {
15729    for (u32 i = 0; i < target.c_targdep_n; i++) {
15730        // mark all elements as not-in-array
15731        target.c_targdep_elems[i]->target_c_targdep_in_ary = false;
15732    }
15733    target.c_targdep_n = 0;
15734}
15735
15736// --- amc.FTarget.c_targdep.qFind
15737// Return reference without bounds checking
15738inline amc::FTargdep& amc::c_targdep_qFind(amc::FTarget& target, u32 idx) {
15739    return *target.c_targdep_elems[idx];
15740}
15741
15742// --- amc.FTarget.c_targdep.InAryQ
15743// True if row is in any ptrary instance
15744inline bool amc::target_c_targdep_InAryQ(amc::FTargdep& row) {
15745    return row.target_c_targdep_in_ary;
15746}
15747
15748// --- amc.FTarget.c_targdep.qLast
15749// Reference to last element without bounds checking
15750inline amc::FTargdep& amc::c_targdep_qLast(amc::FTarget& target) {
15751    return *target.c_targdep_elems[target.c_targdep_n-1];
15752}
15753
15754// --- amc.FTarget..Init
15755// Set all fields to initial values.
15756inline void amc::FTarget_Init(amc::FTarget& target) {
15757    target.c_targdep_elems = NULL; // (amc.FTarget.c_targdep)
15758    target.c_targdep_n = 0; // (amc.FTarget.c_targdep)
15759    target.c_targdep_max = 0; // (amc.FTarget.c_targdep)
15760    target.p_ns = NULL;
15761    target.ind_target_next = (amc::FTarget*)-1; // (amc.FDb.ind_target) not-in-hash
15762}
15763
15764// --- amc.FTarget.c_targdep_curs.Reset
15765inline void amc::target_c_targdep_curs_Reset(target_c_targdep_curs &curs, amc::FTarget &parent) {
15766    curs.elems = parent.c_targdep_elems;
15767    curs.n_elems = parent.c_targdep_n;
15768    curs.index = 0;
15769}
15770
15771// --- amc.FTarget.c_targdep_curs.ValidQ
15772// cursor points to valid item
15773inline bool amc::target_c_targdep_curs_ValidQ(target_c_targdep_curs &curs) {
15774    return curs.index < curs.n_elems;
15775}
15776
15777// --- amc.FTarget.c_targdep_curs.Next
15778// proceed to next item
15779inline void amc::target_c_targdep_curs_Next(target_c_targdep_curs &curs) {
15780    curs.index++;
15781}
15782
15783// --- amc.FTarget.c_targdep_curs.Access
15784// item access
15785inline amc::FTargdep& amc::target_c_targdep_curs_Access(target_c_targdep_curs &curs) {
15786    return *curs.elems[curs.index];
15787}
